U.K. Cuts Could Be Slowed to Support Economy, Padoan Tells FT

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-05-26T00:47:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/u-k-cuts-could-be-slowed-to-support-economy-padoan-tells-ft.html
Pier Carlo Padoan, chief economist of
the Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development, said
slower-than-expected growth in the U.K. suggests the pace of
 deficit reduction  could be slowed in response, the Financial
Times reported, citing an interview. The U.K. government should
be “be selective” in its choice of spending cuts “and their
speed,” he said, according to the FT.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 